 It's a five-minute fix on most tractors and trailers.\"\n          }\n        },\n        {\n          \"@type\": \"Question\",\n          \"name\": \"What is the difference between SAE Class I and Class II for a farm beacon?\",\n          \"acceptedAnswer\": {\n            \"@type\": \"Answer\",\n            \"text\": \"SAE Class I is for vehicles operating near traffic at highway speeds (50+ mph). SAE Class II is for lower-speed environments under 25 mph. For equipment traveling on public roads with speeds above 35 mph, SAE Class I beacons are strongly recommended.\"\n          }\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n</script>"
